Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State has charged political appointees in the state to ensure prudent management of funds and zero tolerance for corruption in the discharge of their responsibilities. He said top government functionaries should be mindful of any manifestation of graft, impropriety and corruption as his administration strove for a stronger state. Speaking at the inauguration of the boards of Delta State Capital Territory Development Agency (DSCTDA) and Warri, Uvwie and Environs Development Agency (WUEDA), yesterday, in Asaba, Okowa stated that political appointees were expected to be transparent while carrying out their activities. According to him, prudent fund management demanded zero tolerance for any manifestation of graft. “I therefore urge you to strive to live above board and employ transparency in the conduct of all your duties as selflessness is key,” he said.  Okowa warns public officers against corruption Baru charges NNPC staff on anti-graft fight, declares zero tolerance Okowa has 2,203 appointees receiving N382m monthly – Commissioner Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin